From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 15:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] backends/logical-monitor: g_return_*_if_fail on accessors

The five thin MetaLogicalMonitor accessors (_get_layout, _get_scale,
_get_transform, _get_number, _is_primary) and _get_monitors do an
unconditional pointer dereference of their @logical_monitor argument.
The contract documents the argument as non-NULL, but in practice many
in-tree callers can be holding NULL because mutter's design legitimately
puts a monitor through transient states where it is "active" (has a
current_mode) but is not in the active MetaMonitorsConfig and therefore
has no logical_monitor association yet. See meta_monitor_update_outputs()
in meta-monitor.c -- it sets logical_monitor to NULL on entry to a
rebuild -- and meta_monitor_manager_rebuild()'s early return at
in_init==TRUE which deliberately skips update_logical_state().

Today's audit (driven by SIGSEGV crashes during HP Reverb G2 hot-plug)
identified at least these unguarded call sites:

  src/wayland/meta-wayland-outputs.c              send_output_events,
                                                  send_xdg_output_events,
                                                  meta_wayland_output_set_monitor
  src/backends/meta-monitor-manager.c             update_current_monitor_mode_scale,
                                                  handle_orientation_change,
                                                  meta_monitor_manager_get_monitor_for_connector
  src/backends/native/meta-cursor-renderer-native.c (cursor scanout fallback)
  src/backends/meta-screen-cast-monitor-stream-src.c (8 sites in screencast)

Rather than patch every callsite as new ones are discovered (and risk
missing future regressions), guard the accessors at the API boundary --
mutter's standard pattern (642 g_return_*_if_fail occurrences in
src/). The chosen defaults are the semantic identity for each return
type:

  _get_layout     -> (MtkRectangle){0,0,0,0}     (empty area)
  _get_scale      -> 1.0f                        (identity scale)
  _get_transform  -> MTK_MONITOR_TRANSFORM_NORMAL (identity transform)
  _get_number     -> -1                          (matches "not found")
  _is_primary     -> FALSE                       (definitionally)
  _get_monitors   -> NULL                        (empty list)

All callers tolerate these defaults: the per-callsite guards we already
have (debian/patches/ubuntu/{wayland-outputs,monitor-manager}-null-check-*)
short-circuit BEFORE reaching the accessor, so this patch is purely
defensive coverage for current and future call sites we have not
explicitly guarded.

When the precondition is violated mutter emits a CRITICAL warning via
g_return_*_if_fail, which makes the bug visible in journal logs rather
than crashing the compositor.

Forwarded: no
Last-Update: 2026-05-20
Index: mutter-50.1/src/backends/meta-logical-monitor.c
===================================================================
--- mutter-50.1.orig/src/backends/meta-logical-monitor.c
+++ mutter-50.1/src/backends/meta-logical-monitor.c
@@ -169,30 +169,41 @@ meta_logical_monitor_add_monitor (MetaLo
 gboolean
 meta_logical_monitor_is_primary (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_val_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL, FALSE);
+
   return logical_monitor->is_primary;
 }
 
 void
 meta_logical_monitor_make_primary (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL);
+
   logical_monitor->is_primary = TRUE;
 }
 
 float
 meta_logical_monitor_get_scale (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_val_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL, 1.0f);
+
   return logical_monitor->scale;
 }
 
 MtkMonitorTransform
 meta_logical_monitor_get_transform (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_val_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL, MTK_MONITOR_TRANSFORM_NORMAL);
+
   return logical_monitor->transform;
 }
 
 MtkRectangle
 meta_logical_monitor_get_layout (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_val_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL,
+                        ((MtkRectangle) { 0, 0, 0, 0 }));
+
   return logical_monitor->rect;
 }
 
@@ -203,11 +214,13 @@ meta_logical_monitor_get_layout (MetaLog
  * Returns the [class@Meta.Monitor]s number which is compatible with the monitor
  * API on [class@Meta.Display] until the next monitors-changed.
  *
- * Returns: The [class@Meta.Monitor]s number
+ * Returns: The [class@Meta.Monitor]s number, or -1 if @logical_monitor is %NULL
  */
 int
 meta_logical_monitor_get_number (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_val_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL, -1);
+
   return logical_monitor->number;
 }
 
@@ -217,12 +230,14 @@ meta_logical_monitor_get_number (MetaLog
  *
  * Returns the list of [class@Meta.Monitor]s.
  *
- * Returns: (transfer none) (element-type Meta.Monitor):
- * The list of [class@Meta.Monitor]s.
+ * Returns: (transfer none) (element-type Meta.Monitor) (nullable):
+ * The list of [class@Meta.Monitor]s, or %NULL if @logical_monitor is %NULL.
  */
 GList *
 meta_logical_monitor_get_monitors (MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor)
 {
+  g_return_val_if_fail (logical_monitor != NULL, NULL);
+
   return logical_monitor->monitors;
 }
 
